# Open features

## Scripting system (Lua)

Allows DMs to write Lua scripts for abilities, encounters, and custom logic.
Scripts call a sandboxed dashboard API. Output goes to the output panel.

### Phase 1 — Output panel
- Add a collapsible output panel at the bottom of the main window (above the status bar)
- Scrollable log with tagged entries: [DICE], [SCRIPT], [SYSTEM]
- Clear button
- No Lua required — phase 1 is purely UI

### Phase 2 — Lua runtime
- Add LuaJ dependency to build.gradle
- Sandbox: strip file I/O, networking, OS calls, load(), loadfile()
- Dashboard API callable from Lua:
    dashboard.roll("2d6+3")           -- resolves dice, prints [DICE] to output, returns number
    dashboard.output("text")          -- prints [SCRIPT] to output
    dashboard.addStatus(name, effect) -- applies status effect to named entity
    dashboard.removeStatus(name, effect)
    dashboard.getEntity(name)         -- returns read-only entity table (stats, position, status)
- Project script (data/scripts/project.lua) loaded at startup if present;
  defines shared functions available to all other scripts

### Phase 3 — Script browser
- data/scripts/ folder holds any .lua files, DM-named, DM-managed
  (bundled with project save/load since it lives inside data/)
- New "Scripts" menu in the menu bar
- "Open Script Browser" lists all .lua files found in data/scripts/
- Click a script to run it; output goes to the panel
- Scripts window stays open until dismissed; re-scannable

### Phase 4 — Entity abilities
- Convention: assets/characters/{name}/abilities.lua auto-discovered by folder name
- Entity right-click on map → "Run Script" → lists ability names from the abilities table
- Clicking an ability runs that specific Lua function
- abilities table format:
    abilities = {
        { name = "Fireball", desc = "8d6 fire damage", run = function() ... end },
    }
- If no abilities.lua exists for the entity, "Run Script" is absent from the menu

---

## Audio device selection
Dropdown at the top of the music bar showing all connected audio output devices.
- Enumerate with javax.sound.sampled.AudioSystem.getMixerInfo() (no extra library needed)
- Requires replacing JavaFX MediaPlayer with javax.sound.sampled for playback
  (MediaPlayer has no device-target API)
- MusicController owns all playback logic — swap is self-contained
- Must be memory-efficient: dispose/re-create Clip or SourceDataLine per device change,
  not per track play

## Named log sessions
Low priority. When enabling logging, optionally prompt for a human-readable session name
(e.g. "Session 5 — Dragon Cave") to use as the session folder name instead of the raw timestamp.
